alachy, Niamh, Seamus.  French Gisele, Julien, Normand, Alain, Armand, Cecile, Clemence, Dominique, Emile, Gilles, Jean-Paul, Laure.","English (Lancashire) and Irish: of Norman origin, a habitational name from Arcy in Manche, France, with fused preposition <i>d(e)</i> ‘from’.","Irish: in Ireland, this is generally the Norman name (see 1 above), established in Meath by Sir William <i>D'Arcy</i> in the 1360s, but it was also adopted for <b>Ó Dorchaidhe</b> ‘descendant of the dark one’, from <i>dorcha</i> ‘dark, gloomy’, a Connacht name that fell together with the Norman surname, which was introduced by Sir William <i>D'Arcy</i> and Sir John <i>D'Arcy</i>, Chief Justiciar of Ireland in the 14th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Darsey","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Darcy   2.","Scottish: from Dairsie in Fife."]},{"name":"Darcey","meanings":["English (of Norman origin) and Irish (Tipperary): variant of   Darcy  ."]}]},{"name":"Katherine","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Katherine ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":17,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":30,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":39,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":84,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Katherine D'Arcy was born in Leeds, Yorkshire, England as the daughter of John Darcy and Baroness Alianore de Holand. She married Sir John Hedworth about 1385, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. She died in 1416, in Sunderland, Durham, England."},"et":{"–1416":"–1416","–1390":"–1390","1375–1425":"1375–1425","1380–1416":"1380–1416","1390–Female":"1390–Surnud","1322–1356":"1322–1356","1315–1341":"1315–1341","about 1390":"umbes 1390","5 March 1356":"5. märts 1356","1341":"1341","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1425":"1425","about 1338":"umbes 1338","1356":"1356","1322":"1322","21 November 1341":"21. november 1341","1453":"1453","1375":"1375","Abt 1385":"umbes 1385","1416":"1416","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Saint-Pierre and Miquelon, New France":"Saint-Pierre, Acadie, Nouvelle-France","Durham, England":"Durham, England","Harraton, Durham, England":"Harraton, Durham, England","Nocton, Lincolnshire, England":"Nocton, Lincolnshire, England","England":"England","Leeds, Yorkshire, England":"Leeds, Yorkshire, England","Sunderland, Durham, England":"Sunderland, Durham, England"},"fi":{"–1416":"–1416","–1390":"–1390","1375–1425":"1375–1425","1380–1416":"1380–1416","1390–Female":"1390–Kuollut","1322–1356":"1322–1356","1315–1341":"1315–1341","about 1390":"noin 1390